s:1107:"<p><span style="font-family:Arial;" lang="en-us" xml:lang="en-us">In order to become an Authorised Officer (AO), a person must first
express an interest through the Regulatory Training Coordinator.  </span></p><p><span style="font-family:Arial;">Good
cause must be demonstrated as to why a person requires authority, which in most
instances will be closely associated to their employment.</span></p><h4></h4><p><span style="font-family:Arial;">Once an expression of interest has been accepted, the applicant will
then be invited to participate in the relevant and required training. 
Successful completion of the required training will result in the person being
able to then make a formal application for authorisation under the Conservation
&amp; Land Management Act (CALM) 1984 and any other associated legislation.</span><br /></p><p></p><h4><span style="font-family:Arial;font-size:12pt;" lang="en-us" xml:lang="en-us">In order for an Authorised
Officer to retain their authority, they <b>must</b> participate and show
competency in annual refresher training.</span>    </h4><p><br /></p>";